      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "`CheckDiskSpace` uses 50 MB as the mimimum free space. With a typical swap gobbling desktop that probably leads to undeterministic behavior, just depending on whether it runs completely out of space.\r\n\r\n50 MB has the additional problem that it's just 3 `rev????.dat` files. I recently had a microSD card for the blocks dir run out of space, and I couldn't start the node anymore even to prune it. I suggest we increase this to a safer 200 MB. Perhaps more if `-prune` isn't set, since the user is doomed to run out space in less than a day.",
      "created_at" : "2019-04-27T19:47:30Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/9997#issuecomment-487314505",
